It is not possible to test debounce using sinon and fake timers:

``` javascript
import test from 'tape';
import sinon from 'sinon';
import debounce from 'lodash.debounce';

test('debounce happy case', t => {
    const clock = sinon.useFakeTimers();
    const spy = sinon.spy();
    const func = debounce(spy, 500);

    func();
    func();
    func();

    clock.tick(499);
    t.ok(spy.notCalled);

    clock.tick(1);
    t.ok(spy.calledOnce); // this fails

    clock.restore();
    t.end();
});
```

This problem is caused because debounce() uses a local copy of Date.now().

